/*!
\page trademgen_drawBookingArrivals
      Script plotting booking arrival curves, as generated by the C++ Simulated Travel Demand Generation Library

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS

<b>trademgen_drawBookingArrivals</b> <tt>[-h|--help] [-o|--output <path-to-output-file>] [-p|--plot] <path-to-input-log-file></tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e trademgen_drawBookingArrivals is a small Python script, extracting the 
   booking requests from the log file produced by the TraDemGen library.
   It produces booking curves, which can even be rendered by a simple
   Matplotlib user interface (when the \b -p/--plot option is given).

\e trademgen_drawBookingArrivals accepts the following options:

 \b -h, \b --help<br>
   Produce that message and show usage.<br>

 \b -o, \b --output <path-to-output-file><br>
   Path to the output file. If blank, the booking curves are dumped onto
   the standard output (stdout).<br>

 \b -p, \b --plot<br>
   Produce a plot, thanks a simple Matplotlib user interface. When that option
   is not given, the booking curves are just dumped onto the output stream.<br>

 \b <path-to-input-log-file><br>
   Path to the input file, i.e., to the log file generated by the \b trademgen
   utility. If blank, the log file is taken from the standard input (stdin).<br>

See the output of the <tt>`trademgen_drawBookingArrivals --help'</tt> command
for default options.


